What I'm Building
An AI-powered stock research agent that takes a ticker symbol (e.g. AAPL, NVDA, TSLA) and autonomously generates a professional analyst-grade research report in under 2 minutes.
Problem It Solves
Professional equity research costs $2,000–$10,000/report and takes analysts 10+ hours. This agent pulls SEC filings, live financials, and news sentiment into one structured report automatically.

My Setup

Windows PC (Dell laptop)
Cursor free version
Python already installed
No Docker — everything runs locally with venv
Starting from scratch


Full Tech Stack

Agent: LangGraph (multi-node StateGraph)
Vector DB: ChromaDB (local)
Embeddings: Sentence Transformers — all-MiniLM-L6-v2
LLM: Groq API — llama-3.1-8b-instant (free tier)
Data Sources: SEC Edgar EFTS API (no key), yfinance (no key), NewsAPI (free tier)
Backend: FastAPI
Frontend: Dash + Dash Bootstrap Components (dark blue theme, accent #60a5fa)
Charts: Plotly Express + Graph Objects
Cache/Storage: SQLite
Evaluation: FinanceBench, ROUGE, custom hallucination checker
No Docker anywhere in this project


