Coding Rules — Always Follow

Python 3.11, type hints everywhere
Pydantic v2 models for all data schemas
Proper try/except with informative error messages
Clean, well-commented code, PEP8 formatting
No Docker anywhere
Always use Windows-compatible terminal commands
One file at a time — build it fully before moving to the next
Every file must have a docstring explaining what it does
Never use placeholder or TODO comments — always write real working code


